intro.description:
		The global properties block contains specifications which are used to describe the entire system. The block starts with the keyword "Global" followed by a list of specifications enclosed in braces { and }. Each specification has to end with a semicolon (;).



Example:

Global {

System name = "Flight Control System";

}


The following specifications can be made within this block:

item.description:
Set the name of the system. It is used in the visualization of the results and the export functionality.


General format:  System name = "[String]";


Example: System name = "Flight Control System";
